$ regat.ps1

`regat.ps1` is a PowerShell script that starts → Windows/dirs/Windows/regedit_exe[`regedit.exe`] and lets it display a given
→ Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[registry key].
This can be achieved by writing the value of the desired key into → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Applets/Regedit/LastKey[the value `LastKey`]
under the registry key
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Applets/Regedit[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Applets\Regedit`]
(see also → Windows/dirs/Windows/regedit_exe#regedit-open-at).

The script recognizes the shortcuts
table { ll
  `userenv` ☰ Opens the registry key that stores the personal → Windows/development/environment-variables[environment variables].
  `machineenv` ☰ Opens the registry key that stores the system environment variables
table }

{ Example invocations

code {
regat hkcu\SOFTWARE\Classes\.gif
regat hklm/software\microsoft
regat hkcu:\Control
regat hkcu:\Control Panel
regat hkcr:\Interface
regat userenv
regat machineenv
code }

}

{ Source code

  gh|scripts-and-utilities|/regat.ps1||

}

{ History

  table { ll
    V.1 ☰ Initial version (2021-08-02)
    V.2 ☰ Replace `hkey_local_machine` with `hklm`, `hkey_current_user` with `hkcu`.
    V.3 ☰ Allow opening keys below → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT[`HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\`] (and add a 'hkcr:' → Windows/PowerShell/language/provider/drive[drive] if necessary)
    V.4 ☰ Use → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters/attributes/parameter/valueFromRemainingArguments[`valueFromRemainingArguments` attribute] on parameter so that registry keys with spaces can be copy-pasted to the command line.
    V.5 ☰ Remove leading `Computer\` from registry key to be opened. (`Computer\` is prepended to a registry key when copying from «address bar» with the → Windows/dirs/Windows/regedit_exe[registry editor `regedit.exe`].
    V.6 ☰ Create registry key `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Windows/CurrentVersion/Applets/Regedit` if it does not exist (2022-07-24)
    → https://github.com/ReneNyffenegger/scripts-and-utilities/commit/487e31e8c901db08121f90f5e086342e657a394a[V.7] ☰ write `hkey_local_machine/` rather than `hklm/` so that the script can be used also in Windows Server 2016. Also replace forward slashes with backslashes before wrting to the registry
  table }

}

